What is the required argument for the `z_importwallet` command?
The required argument for the `z_importwallet` command is the "filename" or the path to the wallet export file.

z_importwallet "filename" Imports taddr and zaddr keys from a wallet export file (see z_exportwallet). Arguments: 1. "filename"  (string, required) The wallet file Examples: Dump the wallet > verus z_exportwallet "nameofbackup" Import the wallet > verus z_importwallet "path/to/exportdir/nameofbackup" Import using the json rpc call > curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "z_importwallet", "params": ["path/to/exportdir/nameofbackup"] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
